        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 5:40PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 539 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Courtland, or 14 miles north of Moulton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 30-40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Decatur, Priceville, Trinity, Courtland, Tanner, Hillsboro,
Mooresville, Belle Mina, and Wheeler.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
